id: problem.auckland.health.maternal_child_health
title: "Maternal and Child Health Disparities"
theme: health
section: health
subpage: maternal-child-health
parent: problem.auckland.health.system_access
order: 3
updated: "2026-04-26"
summary: >
  Preterm birth rates for Maori and Pacific Auckland mothers are 1.5-2
  times those of NZ European mothers. Midwifery vacancy rates in South
  Auckland exceed 30%, reducing antenatal care access for the most
  vulnerable pregnancies. The first 1,000 days represent the highest-
  return public health investment window; current resourcing is
  insufficient to close the gap between high- and low-deprivation
  maternal and child health outcomes.
